    <h1>Developer for Open-Source Research Platform</h1>
  </header>
  <p><a href="https://github.com/tropy">Tropy</a> is a new cross-platform desktop application for managing images of research material. Developed by the same lab that produces <a href="https://github.com/zotero">Zotero</a>, Tropy is an open-source project that creates research software and web services used by humanities scholars worldwide. Thousands are already using Tropy to organize and analyze their documents and artifacts, and Tropy is earning praise and recommendations from research libraries and national archives.</p>
  <p>We’re looking to hire a full-time developer to join our team, where you'll have responsibility over core components of the project and the freedom to find creative solutions to challenging problems. Most importantly, you'll participate in a vibrant global open-source community with amazing community developers and passionate users.</p>
  <p>Your work will be based out of Roy Rosenzweig Center for History and New Media, a leading center for digital humanities that’s internationally recognized for its innovative open-source software. You’ll communicate with Tropy developers and users via online workspaces, forums, and GitHub.</p>
  <h2 class="h4">Requirements:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Extensive experience with modern JavaScript, especially with Electron, Node.js and React</li>
    <li>Experience with command-line Linux/Unix systems and services</li>
    <li>Comfort using version control and CI platforms</li>
    <li>Strong attention to privacy and security issues</li>
    <li>Willingness to participate in an open-source community</li>
  </ul>
  <h2 class="h4">Bonus:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>A strong design sense and familiarity with modern CSS</li>
    <li>Experience developing desktop applications for Linux, macOS and/or Windows</li>
    <li>Experience working with WebGL and HTML Canvas</li>
    <li>Experience working with linked data and the semantic web (RDF, JSON-LD)</li>
    <li>Experience working with and/or developing web APIs (HTTP/REST/JSON)</li>
    <li>Experience building user-friendly software and websites used by many people or the back-end services powering them, or both</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Please send a cover letter and résumé, including relevant programming projects and experience, to <a href="mailto:jobs@tropy.org">jobs@tropy.org</a> with subject line “Tropy Developer.” We will begin considering applications immediately and continue until the position is filled. Applications without a cover letter will not be considered.</p>
